text: Temuco is a Chilean city with 245,347 inhabitants (2002 census). == History == Temuco was founded by Manuel Recabarren naming the place Fuerte Recabarren(Fort Recabarren) during the Occupation of Araucania on 1881. == Gallery == File:Interior Rodoviario Temuco.jpg|The Bus Station of Temuco File:Edificio_Caupolicán.jpg|Caupolicán Tower File:Temuco.jpg|Skyline of Temuco == References == ==Other websites== *Temuco municipality Category:Cities in Chile Category:Araucanía Region Category:Capitals of Chilean regions
